Total Arms Exports of China, France, the United States and Russia. (2011-2015).
➖
The maps are based on figures for 2011-2015, published by the Stockholm International Peace Research Institute (SIPRI). They exclude weapons trade deals below $100 million. The total volume of arms sales for this period was higher than for any other five-year stretch since the end of the Cold war, in the early 1990s.
➖
The United States not only has the world's largest defence budget by far (1), it also outsells all other countries by a considerable margin. For the aforementioned period, American weapons exports were worth $46.4 billion, almost a third of the global total (32.8%). Russia’s amounted to $35,4 billion, representing just over a quarter of the global arms trade (25.3%). The margin between both is more than what numbers three and four each earn on their arms trading: France made $8,1 billion, while China raked in $7,9 billion.
➖
Each of the four maps mentions the five major recipients of that country's arms exports – providing a peek into each exporter’s geopolitical priorities. As for America, they seem to be in the Middle East, mainly. The five biggest buyers of U.S. military hardware were, in descending order: Saudi Arabia ($4.6 billion), the United Arab Emirates ($4.2 billion), Turkey ($3.1 billion), South Korea ($3.1 billion) and Australia ($2.9 billion). In all, America sold more than $100 million worth of arms to 42 countries, many of them also in the Middle East.
➖
Russia and India have the single-biggest bilateral arms trade relationship in the world, at least for the period described here. From 2011 up to and including 2015, New Delhi bought for $13.4 billion in arms from the Russians. And despite being a major exporter itself, even China acquired a lot of Russian weaponry, to the tune of $3.8 billion. Vietnam stocked up on Russian arms for almost the same amount ($3.7 billion). Other large recipients of Russian weapons were Algeria ($2.6 billion) and Venezuela ($1.9 billion).
➖

I recently had a new follower tell me this..
"I just gained so much respect for you" .. becaus so many profiles are filled with women who's bio says "Saved By Grace" .. then you scroll through their photo's and instantly feel like you need to put the phone down, scrub your eye's with soap and ask God to forgive you for seeing that .. What has happened to modesty these days!? ..I listened to a #PaulWasher Sermon a couple nights back and this is what I wrote down...⤵ "WHO DO I IMITATE?" & "DO I LOOK LIKE THE WORLD?" ..God has called us to be like who..? Every other girl from Hollywood we see on tv? 
The girl down the street? 
The girl on instagram? ..
The girl from that movie? ..NO! He has called us to be different!
To be like HIM! Let me tell ya, I would rather strive to be like Jesus then that girl on tv. The people on tv will change with the style, Jesus will NEVER CHANGE! 
Although.. it is hard when you see some pretty face with their hair done cute, makeup on point etc. and inside you feel this prick... a prick in your heart (from satan none the less) that says "hey, you should be like her, all the guys like her, and she is better than you,  you're nothing compared to her" .. but God says "No, be different, be like ME!" This life as a Christian is NOT about us, it's all about Jesus! And telling other's about Jesus and how to be saved!  We need to strive to BE LIKE JESUS! Not the people you see on tv... Ask God to mold you into what He wants! 
You won't regret it! 
And also... when you get dressed ask yourself "Will this cause someone (a man) to stumble, will it cause a woman to look down at her toes and feel that prick?  Maybe some women don't think like that.. but it's definitely an area I need to work on (comparison).. who's with me?  Instead of looking to others to compare ourselves,  let's strive to see how little we really are like Jesus and strive to be more like Him!

Life gets messy. Our house is littered with toys 99.9% of the time. I am currently washing laundry but haven't put away of the clothes for the last load (that I did 4 days ago 😳). I haven't brushed my hair yet (or showered). And our usual "sleep until 9:30 kiddo" was up at 6. But, we have had a lot of laughs and shared a lot of cuddles today already. I'm never too worried about if all the laundry is sorted or the house is in order. Because the days are flying by, and I don't want to miss a thing! So let the clothes keep spinning in the dryer. We are going to scatter more toys and play. None of us are perfect. I look like a homeless person 6 days a week 🙈 but I honestly don't even care. We are all doing our best. Let's not judge each other for our difference. Let's encourage and support and love each other instead. Life is too short to spend it comparing yourself to anyone else. 💗💗💗
Everyone has a different journey. Don't waste your valuable time comparing yourself to others.

A handful of Almonds vs. A packet of Fruit Pastels 🍬⠀
⠀
Both snacks have the same calories. Which one would you pick?⠀
⠀
Occasionally I’m the left hand, but mostly I’m the right hand. (I know, shocking. A person who considers themselves into health and fitness eats sweets - and is openly talking about it on social media.) 🌝🌝🌝⠀
⠀
You see, although I’m fully aware that a handful of almonds contains lots of wonderful nutrients that would keep me fuller for longer, some days (no matter whether I’m looking to gain, maintain or lose weight) I’ll choose to eat sweets or a chocolate bar as a snack 💪⠀
⠀
Why? Because when the majority of my diet has consisted of well-balanced food that’s full of micronutrients, I have no issue eating something thats less so just because I love the taste of it. This is just a personal choice. Cutting out things I love isn’t realistic for me so I always squeeze something sweet into my days (all whilst still sticking to my calorie/macro/micro targets.)⠀
⠀
Many would choose the almonds for the nutritional value or the flavour - which is totally fine. Many would choose the almonds because even though they'd prefer Fruit Pastels, almonds would make them feel more ‘on track’ mentally - which again, is totally fine 💕⠀
⠀
I’m not glorifying sweets, or almonds for that matter. I’m glorifying knowing what’s in the food you’re eating, and make educated decisions based on your own values. And I value food that’s good for my body and good for my soul.⠀
⠀
‘Healthy' to me is exactly what I make it. And Fruit Pastels (in moderation) make me happy which I believe contributes largely to my overall health 🙌⠀
⠀

we've always been so cute wow (2015-2017)

I spent my entire 20's abusing my body, taking it for granted. I spent my entire adult life in a body I didn't feel comfortable in. And as the years went by, I was more self conscious. Hiding from pictures, hiding in baggy clothes.
The picture on the left was taken the summer of 2007. 10 years ago. I wasn't at my biggest, because I remember wearing size 18 pants. I couldn't tell you what I weighed. I was 22 years old.
Fast forward to today. I still have my flaws that I get bothered by. I'm not where I want to be, but I am so far from where I once was. I have a confidence in myself that I've never experienced in my life. And this goes beyond just looking good. Confidence as a whole in life. Not questioning myself, not afraid to go after what I want. Today, at 32, I'm healthier than I've ever been.. physically + mentally. I'm a constant work in progress. We all are. The amazing thing is every day we are given a new chance to progress, to go after the things we want in life. Don't let it pass you by. Whether it's weight loss, fitness, health related, etc.. whatever it is.. DO IT. Life is too short. 💖
Again, one of those moments I have a million thoughts going through & I type quick. So if it doesn't fully make sense.. SORRY. I've had too much coffee too. So. 😂
